I get the plastic ones; Chameleon Cold Brew Vanilla, and I looove it

The plastic bottles of the chameleon coffee are not as concentrated. The glass bottles definitely taste better IMO! But i switched to making my own cold brew in half gallon ball mason jars and organic coffee beans.  I just grind the beans using a burr grinder, fill 1/4 of whatever jar I’m using with the coffee, top with water and then leave it out in the counter for like 24 hrs, strain and you have cold brew! More labor intensive but definitely cheaper and I switch up the flavors by using different beans, or adding different extracts or home made flavored simple syrup!
